  "local_port": 53686,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do I eat on the Ketogenics Diet?",
  "response": "The ketogenic diet is a high-fat, moderate-protein, and very low-carbohydrate eating plan. It aims to induce a state of ketosis in the body, where fat is burned for energy instead of carbohydrates. Here's a general idea of what you can eat on a ketogenic diet:\n\n1. **Fats and Oils**:\n   - Healthy oils like olive oil, coconut oil, and avocado oil\n   - Butter and ghee\n   - Lard and tallow\n\n2. **Protein Sources**:\n   - Meat: beef, pork, lamb, poultry\n   - Fatty fish: salmon, sardines, mackerel\n   - Eggs\n\n3. **Dairy** (full-fat options):\n   - Cheese\n   - Cream\n   - Greek yogurt\n\n4. **Low-Carb Vegetables**:\n   - Leafy greens: spinach, kale, arugula\n   - Cruciferous vegetables: broccoli, cauliflower, cabbage\n   - Zucchini, asparagus, bell peppers\n\n5. **Nuts and Seeds**:\n   - Almonds, walnuts, pecans\n   - Chia seeds, flaxseeds, pumpkin seeds\n\n6. **Beverages**:\n   - Water\n   - Coffee and tea (unsweetened)\n   - Bone broth\n\n7. **Other**:\n   - Avocados\n   - Olives\n   - Berries (in moderation)\n\n**Foods to Avoid**:\n- Grains: rice, wheat, oats\n- Sugar: desserts, sodas, candies\n- High-carb fruits: bananas, grapes, apples\n- Starchy vegetables: potatoes, sweet potatoes, corn\n- Beans and legumes\n\nIt's important to ensure you're getting a balanced intake of nutrients and to consider consulting with a healthcare provider before starting the diet, especially if you have health conditions or concerns.",
